  - id: 
    title: 'Case Number: MSP-2018-0701-441'
    body: "Incident Type: Fatal Traffic Collision\LDate of Incident: July 1, 2018\LLocation:
      Interstate 93 Northbound, near South Bay Interchange, Boston, Massachusetts\nVictim:
      Daniel Reed (34)\nSuspect: Travis Cole (42)\nIncident happened around 19:30.
      Witness reported that Travis accelerated while approaching traffic ahead before
      striking the rear of Daniel's car at highway speed.\nThe impact caused the
      victim's vehicle to lose directional control, spin across the lane, and collide
      with the highway barrier.\nDriver remained at the scene and cooperated with
      responding officers. In his initial statement, driver reported that he failed
      to reduce speed in time when approaching the vehicle ahead, resulting in a
      rear-end collision. \n"
    appType: 1
    keywords:
    - Daniel Reed
    - daniel reed
  - id: 
    title: QuantLog Analytics
    body: "We are a U.S.-based clinical data management and biostatistics company
      headquartered in Cambridge, Massachusetts. We provide data infrastructure,
      statistical analysis, and regulatory reporting services for pharmaceutical
      and biotechnology companies conducting clinical trials.\nServices\nQuantLog
      Analytics provides a range of services related to clinical trial data management
      and analysis, including:\nClinical database design and maintenance\nElectronic
      case report form (eCRF) systems\nBiostatistical analysis\n \nContact us: JuanLev@quantlog.com"
    appType: 0
    keywords:
    - QuantLog Analytics
    - quantlog analytics
    - quantlog
    - QuantLog
  - id: 
    title: "Wekipedia\u2014\u2014QuantLog"
    body: "QuantLog Analytics\nQuantLog Analytics is a U.S.-based clinical data management
      and biostatistics company headquartered in Cambridge, Massachusetts. The firm
      provides data infrastructure, statistical analysis, and regulatory reporting
      services for pharmaceutical and biotechnology companies conducting clinical
      trials.\nFounded in 2009, QuantLog specializes in managing large-scale clinical
      datasets and supporting drug developers through the statistical and regulatory
      stages of late-phase clinical research.\nThe company is part of the broader
      contract research organization (CRO) ecosystem that supports pharmaceutical
      development.\nRole in Clinical Development\nPharmaceutical companies frequently
      outsource clinical data processing to specialized CRO firms such as QuantLog.
      In this role, QuantLog works alongside clinical operations teams and regulatory
      consultants to ensure that trial data are:\nconsistent\ntraceable\ncompliant
      with regulatory requirements\nThese datasets are ultimately used in New Drug
      Applications (NDA) submitted to regulatory agencies such as the U.S. Food and
      Drug Administration (FDA).\nIndustry Position\nQuantLog Analytics operates
      within the Boston\u2013Cambridge biotechnology cluster, one of the largest
      life sciences research hubs in the world.\nThe company has developed partnerships
      with multiple pharmaceutical developers and research institutions in the region.\nAmong
      the pharmaceutical companies that have contracted QuantLog for clinical data
      services is Elixir Biopharma, a cardiovascular drug developer headquartered
      in Cambridge."
    appType: 0
    keywords:
    - QuantLog Analytics
    - quantlog analytics
    - quantlog
    - QuantLog
