  - id: 
    title: QuantLog Data Manager Reported Missing; Police Investigating Possible
      Corporate Data Theft
    body: "July 6\nAuthorities in Cambridge have launched an investigation after
      a senior employee of QuantLog Analytics was reported missing earlier this week.\nThe
      individual, identified as Juan Lev, 41, worked as a Senior Data Operations
      Manager at the company\u2019s Cambridge headquarters.\nAccording to a statement
      released by QuantLog, the company reported Lev missing after he failed to report
      to work and could not be reached by phone or email for several days.\nPossible
      Removal of Company Materials\nCambridge Police confirmed that the case is being
      investigated in coordination with the company\u2019s internal security team.\nA
      spokesperson for the Cambridge Police Department stated that Lev had access
      to clinical research data systems and internal project documentation through
      his role. Investigators are examining whether Lev may have left the company
      while in possession of sensitive corporate materials."
    appType: 0
    keywords:
    - Juan Lev
    - Juan
    - juan
    - juan lev
  - id: 
    title: 'Case Number: CPD-2018-0706-302'
    body: "Case Type: Missing Person / Possible Corporate Data Theft\LDate Opened:
      July 16, 2018\LJurisdiction: Cambridge, Massachusetts Name: Juan Lev\LAge:
      41\LOccupation: Senior Data Operations Manager\LEmployer: QuantLog Analytics\LResidence:
      Somerville, Massachusetts Lev was reported missing by his employer after failing
      to appear for work and being unreachable by phone and email for several days.
      QuantLog representatives informed that Lev had administrative access to several
      clinical data systems and internal project documentation as part of his employment
      responsibilities. The company expressed concern that Lev may have removed proprietary
      materials prior to leaving. Last Known Timeline July 1, 2018  20:04 \u2014
      Lev logged into QuantLog internal network from office workstation.\L 20:10
      \u2014 Access recorded in several project directories related to ongoing clinical
      data operations.\L 22:05 \u2014 Security records show Lev exiting the QuantLog
      Cambridge facility.\L 22:13 \u2014 Building surveillance captured Lev leaving
      the parking structure. Lev has not been seen at the workplace since that time.
      Recent Call Activity June 28, 2018 08:14 Outgoing (857) 555-4478 03:12 June
      30, 2018 09:22 Incoming (781) 555-1140 00:10 July 1, 2018 16:45 Outgoing (781)
      555-2356 04:29 July 1, 2018 19:20 Outgoing (617) 555-7821 01:08 July 1, 2018
      19:35 Incoming (617) 555-7821 03:45  Additional Notes Investigators found a
      file recently uploaded onto Juan's ClouDisk, protected with password. File
      link"
    appType: 0
    keywords:
    - Juan Lev
    - juan lev
  - id: 
    title: Help Emily Fight for Her Life
    body: "Created: March 12, 2018\LLocation: Quincy, Massachusetts\nHi everyone,\nMy
      name is Travis Cole, and I never thought I would find myself writing something
      like this.\nI\u2019m a single father raising my daughter Emily, who just turned
      9 years old this spring. Emily is the kindest and bravest kid I know. She loves
      drawing animals, watching space documentaries, and telling me about the planets
      she wants to visit one day.\nLast year, Emily was diagnosed with a rare congenital
      blood disorder that affects how her body forms clots. What started as frequent
      bruising and unexplained fatigue quickly turned into a series of hospital visits,
      tests, and treatments.\nDoctors told us that Emily will likely need long-term
      medication and specialized treatment to manage the condition, which is extremely
      expensive for my family. Without it, even minor injuries could become life-threatening.\nI
      work full time and do everything I can to support my daughter, but the reality
      is that I can\u2019t do this alone. If you are able to help, any contribution\u2014no
      matter how small\u2014will go directly toward Emily\u2019s medical care and
      treatment. If you cannot donate, sharing this page would mean the world to
      us.\nI just want to make sure she gets the chance to grow up.\nThank you for
      taking the time to read our story.\nTop Comment\nJuan L    $500\n Stay strong,
      man. Emily needs you.\n \u2003\u2003\u2003Author replied: Thanks, man. You've
      always been a good friend.\nSarah M   $100\n Try applying for the ECAP. Stay
      strong!\n\u2003\u2003\u2003Author replied: Thank you! We actually tried applying
      for that but they turned us down.\n            John C replied: ECAP is shit.
      Only few people got accepted into the project. Hypocrites!\n"
    appType: 0
    keywords:
    - Travis Cole
    - travis cole
    - travis
    - Travis
