  - id: 
    title: "Wekipedia\u2014\u2014ECAP"
    body: "Elixir Compassion Access Program Elixir Compassion Access Program (ECAP)
      is a patient assistance and charitable access initiative operated by Elixir
      Biopharma. Established in 2014, the program provides subsidized or no-cost
      treatment support to selected patients with serious chronic illnesses, rare
      disorders, and long-term cardiovascular conditions who are unable to afford
      standard therapy. ECAP was launched as part of Elixir\u2019s broader corporate
      social responsibility and patient access strategy, and has been cited by the
      company as evidence of its commitment to reducing cost barriers in life-sustaining
      care. Controversy among public While publicly described by the company as a
      program aimed at expanding access to life-saving medication, the Elixir Compassion
      Access Program has been criticized for its restrictive eligibility requirements
      and limited acceptance rate. Critics argue that such programs can function
      as corporate reputation initiatives, allowing pharmaceutical companies to highlight
      charitable efforts while continuing to sell high-cost medications at market
      prices."
    appType: 0
    keywords:
    - ECAP
    - ecap
  - id: 
    title: Elixir Compassion Access Program (ECAP)
    body: "Expanding access. Supporting patients. Strengthening care.\nAt Elixir
      Biopharma, we believe that no patient should be left behind because of financial
      hardship.\nThe Elixir Compassion Access Program (ECAP) was created to help
      eligible patients and families gain access to treatment support when cost becomes
      a barrier to care. Through ECAP, Elixir works with healthcare providers and
      patient families to reduce out-of-pocket burden for selected therapies in areas
      of significant unmet medical need.\nOur Commitment\nSerious and chronic illnesses
      place an enormous burden on patients, caregivers, and families. In many cases,
      treatment decisions are shaped not only by medical need, but by affordability.\nECAP
      reflects Elixir\u2019s commitment to:\nimproving treatment access for underserved
      patients\nsupporting families facing long-term care costs\npartnering with
      physicians to help patients remain on therapy\nadvancing a more affordable
      future in chronic disease care\nFor Elixir, access is not separate from innovation.
      It is part of innovation.\nWho ECAP Supports\nECAP may provide assistance to
      qualifying patients in selected therapeutic areas, including:\ncardiovascular
      care\nanticoagulation and clotting-related conditions\nhematological disorders\nselected
      chronic metabolic conditions\nSupport may include:\nreduced-cost treatment
      access\ntemporary no-cost supply programs\ncase review for hardship circumstances\npatient
      support coordination through treating physicians\nPeople We Helped\n\uFF08Pictures
      of patients, including Emily Cole.\uFF09\nApply Through Your Healthcare Provider\nECAP
      applications must be submitted by a licensed healthcare provider or authorized
      clinical office representative.\nFor program inquiries, physicians and care
      teams may contact:\nECAP Patient Access Office\L Elixir Biopharma\L Cambridge,
      Massachusetts\L Phone: (800) 555-2741\L Email: ecap@elixirbiopharma.com"
    appType: 0
    keywords:
    - ECAP
    - ecap
  - id: 
    title: Atlantic Supply Distribution
    body: "Atlantic Supply Distribution is a regional logistics and equipment transport
      company based in Quincy, Massachusetts, serving commercial, industrial, and
      research clients across the Greater Boston area.\nFounded in 2001, the company
      specializes in the transport of high-value equipment, technical hardware, and
      laboratory supplies for clients in technology research and industrial sectors.\nAtlantic
      Supply Distribution operates a fleet of light and medium transport vehicles
      and provides scheduled delivery services to universities, corporate campuses,
      and research facilities throughout Massachusetts and neighboring states.\nClients\nWe
      have been working with many companies and organizations you might heard of,
      such as QuantLog Analytics, and we receive positive reviews from them. \nAt
      ASD, we put our clients' interest in first place."
    appType: 0
    keywords:
    - Atlantic Supply Distribution
    - atlantic supply distribution
  - id: 
    title: "Wekipedia\u2014\u2014Elixir Biopharma"
    body: "Elixir Biopharma is an American multinational pharmaceutical company headquartered
      in Cambridge, Massachusetts. Founded in 1984, the company is known for developing
      therapies in cardiovascular medicine, anticoagulation, and metabolic disease.\nThroughout
      the 1990s and early 2000s, Elixir grew into one of the leading pharmaceutical
      manufacturers in the United States, largely driven by a series of successful
      cardiovascular drugs. \nAs of 2018, Elixir employs approximately 18,000 people
      worldwide and maintains research and manufacturing facilities across North
      America and Europe.\nTherapeutic Focus\nElixir Biopharma primarily develops
      treatments in the following areas:\nCardiovascular medicine\nAnticoagulation
      therapies\nMetabolic disease treatments\nVascular health\nMany of the company's
      most successful drugs have been used to prevent blood clots, strokes, and heart
      attacks in patients with cardiovascular conditions.\nMajor Products\nThromval\nApproved:
      1998\L Indication: Prevention of blood clots in patients with atrial fibrillation.\nThromval
      became one of the most widely prescribed anticoagulants in North America during
      the early 2000s.\nCardiox\nApproved: 2003\L Indication: Treatment of chronic
      hypertension.\nCardiox was a major commercial success and remained a leading
      therapy for over a decade.\nUnknown Project (in development)\nEstimated approval
      time: 2018\n"
    appType: 0
    keywords:
    - Elixir
    - elixir
    - Elixir Biopharma
    - elixir biopharma
  - id: 
    title: Elixir Biopharma Expected to Transition Clinical Data Management Partner
    body: "May 26\nElixir Biopharma is reportedly preparing to transition its clinical
      trial data infrastructure to a new contract research partner. Industry observers
      say the company is now evaluating alternative vendors as part of a broader
      review of its clinical data systems and regulatory preparation processes.\nDr.
      Karen Whitmore, Elixir\u2019s Vice President of Clinical Operations, addressed
      the company\u2019s ongoing clinical data infrastructure modernization during
      a recent industry conference panel. Whitmore stated that the company is focused
      on ensuring that its clinical data pipelines remain \u201Cfully aligned with
      evolving regulatory expectations.\u201D\nQuantLog Analytics has served as a
      clinical data contractor for multiple Elixir research programs, providing database
      management and statistical data preparation services for regulatory submissions.\nWhitmore
      did not comment directly on the status of the company\u2019s relationship with
      QuantLog Analytics. Neither company has confirmed if / when a potential transition
      would take place."
    appType: 0
    keywords:
    - Elixir
    - elixir
    - Elixir Biopharma
    - elixir biopharma
