  - id: 
    title: 'Case Number: CPD-2018-0119-117 '
    body: "Case Type: Sudden Death Investigation\LDate Opened: January 19, 2018\nDate
      Closed: March 14, 2018\LLocation: Cambridge, Massachusetts\nIncident Summary\n5
      persons enrolled in a clinical trial for an investigational anticoagulant medication
      identified as HXR-217, administered as part of a Phase III cardiovascular study
      conducted at Cambridge Heart Research Center. Within 4 months after treatments
      started, these 5 patients deceased because of severe bleeding symptoms. The
      families of these 5 patients now request a full investigation on Elixir's clinical
      trial.\nMedical Findings\nHospital physicians reported evidence of severe internal
      bleeding, including:\nsuspected intracranial hemorrhage\nsignificant blood
      loss\nabnormal clotting parameters\n\n\n\n\n\nInvestigator Notes\nInvestigators
      determined that the death occurred in the context of a registered clinical
      trial and that no evidence of criminal activity was present. The subjects had
      voluntarily enrolled in the trial and bleeding complications were a documented
      risk of anticoagulant medication. Besides, the subjects had been confirmed
      to have not followed the prescribed dosing instructions. \nThe subjects' families
      confirmed that they have come to an agreement with Elixir Biopharma, thus no
      further investigation is needed."
    appType: 1
    keywords:
    - Elixir
    - elixir
    - Elixir Biopharma
    - elixir biopharma
